			<div class='contents_body_padding_1'>&nbsp;</div>
			<div class='contents_body_output'>
				<p>
					I'm an open source artist living with <a href='http://dystonia-dreams.org/index.php?View=Support%20Groups&Writing=314'>Generalized Dystonia</a>. I feel coding is one of my main art forms &amp; forms of self expression.
				</p><p>
					My podcast . . . videos . . . animations . . . portfolio . . . community . . . &amp;more . . . all coming soon!
				</p><p>
					My podcast, here, will focus on the art that is programming.&nbsp; Especially when it comes to coding as a form of free &amp;self expression.&nbsp; Just like one's ability to express themselves should always be free.&nbsp; This is the *free* part of Free &amp;Open Source Software(F&amp;OSS) or any Reciprocal System, Service, Software, &amp;Societies.
				</p><p>
					I'm really an uberChick &amp;have my nerd woman brain wrinkles into a lot of everything.&nbsp; Coding/Hacking/Programming/Software Engineering/Etc.&nbsp; My favorite languages include C, PHP, Perl, XML, XLS Family of Languages, CSS, JavaScript, XHTML, RSS, Mono, LUA, &amp;many others.&nbsp; My broad range of interests &amp;talents include graphic, 3D, game, &amp;web design; animation, video, &amp;audio production; writing blogs, essays, &amp;white papers; databases like MySQL, SQLite3, XML/XQuery, &amp;many many many other forms of art.
				</p><p>
					Using my constantly growing array of art tools &amp;canvases.&nbsp; My art works, projects, &amp;creations are constantly growing.&nbsp; &amp;Just like any other <a href='http://uberChicks.Net/'>uberChicks</a>my interests, art forms, &amp;forms of self expression are as limitless as my imagination, motivations, &amp;emotions.&nbsp; Which is a true gift; though I&#039;m still working on embracing all of my aspects, interests, &amp;goals.&nbsp; In a way that will make a true difference.
				</p><p>
					Right now my programming is focused mostly on internet programs.&nbsp; My project that I'm focusing on the most is web/browser based, though not exclusively.&nbsp; Most of my projects are internet based, e.g. XULRunner applications, &not; exclusively web based.
				</p>
			</div>
